Functional Test Report

Application Name: Scandium Web App
Testing Type: Functional Testing
Audience: Client-Facing
Test Cycle: Release 1.0
Prepared By: Zay Zay
Test Date: December 2025

1. Executive Summary

This report documents the results of functional testing conducted on the Scandium Web App, a client-facing web application. The objective of this testing was to verify that all key functionalities operate as per business and functional requirements and that the application is stable and ready for client use.

Testing was completed successfully with major functionalities working as expected. A small number of minor defects were identified and logged, none of which block production release.

2. Test Objectives

The primary objectives of functional testing were to:

Validate core application features against functional requirements

Ensure correct user interactions and workflows

Verify data accuracy and system responses

Identify functional defects before production deployment

Confirm readiness for client-facing usage

3. Test Scope
In Scope

User registration and login

Dashboard access and navigation

Data input forms and validation

Logout and session handling

Error messages and system notifications

Out of Scope

Performance testing

Security / penetration testing

Compatibility testing on unsupported browsers

Backend database validation beyond UI confirmation

4. Test Environment

Component	Details
Application URL	Scandium Web App (Staging)
Environment	Staging
Browser(s)	Chrome, Firefox
Operating System	Windows 11, Linux
Testing Type	Manual Functional Testing

5. Test Approach

Test cases were designed based on functional requirements

Manual testing was performed using positive and negative test scenarios

Defects were documented with steps to reproduce and expected vs actual results

Retesting was conducted for fixed issues where applicable

6. Test Execution Summary

Metric	Count
Total Test Cases	45
Passed	39
Failed	4
Blocked	NA
Not Executed	0

7. Defect Summary
Severity	Count
Critical	0
High	0
Medium	2
Low	2
Notable Issues

High: 

Medium: Incorrect validation message displayed for empty mandatory fields

Low: UI alignment issue on dashboard widgets

All identified defects have been logged and communicated to the development team. (simulation purpose)

8. Risk Assessment

Minor UI issues may impact user experience but not functionality

No data loss or security-related risks identified during functional testing

9. Recommendations

Fix and retest the identified  defect

Conduct UAT with real client scenarios

Perform regression testing after defect fixes

Plan security testing prior to production deployment


10. Test Conclusion & Sign-Off


Based on the results of functional testing, the Scandium Web App is conditionally approved for release, pending resolution of high and medium severity defects.

Once fixes are verified, the application will be ready for client-facing production use.

